 PRETORIA - Gauteng's acting Social Development MEC Panyaza Lesufi says the department underestimated the number of homeless people in the province. Lesufi visited a site in Pretoria on Wednesday where homeless people are being accommodated for the lockdown. SA lockdown: Shortage of tents for Cape Town homeless The MEC said the provincial government are determined to get everyone off the streets in a bid to fight the spread of COVID-19. In Johannesburg, about 2,000 vulnerable people are being housed in shelters and relocated to temporary accommodation but, this is a far bigger problem to grapple with. READ: SA lockdown: Johannesburg homeless being sheltered An estimated 13,000 homeless people still need to be found and relocated to temporary shelters. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.